The paper focuses on outlier mining in a streaming environment, which involves handling large amounts of data and requires efficient algorithms. This suggests that the paper may belong to the database (cs.DB), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of massively parallel systems, which falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents technical challenges and alternatives, which may be relevant to the computer engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
